Reasoning: The paper analyzes the impact of social media campaigns during the 2016 US presidential election, specifically on Twitter. This falls under the categories of social media analysis (cs.SOC), cybersecurity (cs.CYBER), and information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also uses graph analysis techniques to study the diffusion cascades of web and media context, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the spread of misinformation and inflammatory political content, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
